content: Hi my name is Andrés Testi. I'm a Rust project follower since 2014. This year I was on the Rust Latam conf at Montevideo, and my interest in rust grew a lot. Lately, I have been working on a personal compiler project, wrote a parser in nom 5.0 with WASM as backend. I gained a lot of experience with this project, but want to improve my Rust skills even more. My area of interest is WASM, but It's not exclusive, I could help with anything, since I really like this project and community, and want to collaborate with you.
hi @Andrés Testi, there are these E-mentor and E-easy issues on the issue tracker
I have some tasks too but couldn't still write those down and it may take a while

you can also jump in https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/122652-new-members and introduce yourself, usually you would expose to more people that can figure out a bit your background and hand other better things to do
